  "topic_goal": "Teach continuity at a point, discontinuity types, and the Intermediate Value Theorem with proofs of existence for roots and fixed points.",
  "topic_takeaways": [
    "Continuity at a requires f(a) defined, limit exists, and they match.",
    "Classify removable, jump, and infinite discontinuities before invoking IVT.",
    "IVT guarantees a crossing when f is continuous on [a,b] and N is strictly between endpoint values.",
    "Always verify continuity on the entire closed interval, endpoint bracketing alone is not enough.",
    "Session 2 limits arc complete; derivatives begin with instantaneous rate of change."
